# TypeScript Guidelines

## Types
- Prefer interfaces for object shapes
- Explicit return types for exported functions

## Code Style
- Small, pure functions; guard clauses
- No mutation of inputs; avoid any

## Errors
- Throw Error with descriptive messages

## Modules
- Prefer named exports; avoid default unless justified
